      "content": "I firmly believe that while some economists raise valid concerns, protectionist tariffs can be a strategic and necessary tool, especially for safeguarding national security, promoting industrial growth, and maintaining jobs. The debate between free trade and protectionism has a lot of layers, but in my view, the protectionist stance isn't just a single-sided narrative—it's an integral part of a broader, complex economic strategy considering both the immediate and long-term needs of a country. So yes, empirical evidence shows costs, but there's also a strategic defense of domestic industries to consider.",
